00:49:00,451 --> 00:49:01,872
Mr. Cohaagen.

488
00:49:09,210 --> 00:49:11,090
You wanted to see me, sir?

489
00:49:14,757 --> 00:49:19,655
Richter, do you know why I'm such a happy person?

490
00:49:19,720 --> 00:49:21,100
No, sir.

491
00:49:22,815 --> 00:49:26,357
Because I've got the greatest job in the solar system.

492
00:49:26,360 --> 00:49:30,528
As long as the turbinium keeps flowing,
I can do anything I want.

493
00:49:30,531 --> 00:49:31,911
Anything.

494
00:49:33,609 --> 00:49:38,679
If fact, the only thing I ever worry about is that one day,...

495
00:49:38,697 --> 00:49:43,541
...if the rebels win, it all might end.

496
00:49:43,702 --> 00:49:45,207
And you're fucking making it happen!

497
00:49:46,205 --> 00:49:49,248
First you try to kill Quaid,
and then you let him get away.

498
00:49:49,250 --> 00:49:51,464
He had help from our side, sir.

499
00:49:52,753 --> 00:49:53,883
I know that.

500
00:49:56,048 --> 00:49:58,424
- But I thought--
- Who told you to think?

501
00:49:58,426 --> 00:50:01,612
I don't give you enough information to think.

502
00:50:03,055 --> 00:50:06,825
You do what you're told.
That's what you do.

503
00:50:08,894 --> 00:50:10,107
Yes, sir.

504
00:50:15,568 --> 00:50:17,073
Now let's get down to business.

505
00:50:18,863 --> 00:50:21,160
We've got a tricky situation here.

506
00:50:21,282 --> 00:50:23,579
Kuato wants what's in Quaid's head.

507
00:50:24,994 --> 00:50:28,430
And he might be able to get it,
cause they say he's psychic.

508
00:50:29,749 --> 00:50:32,768
And I have a plan to keep this from happening.

509
00:50:36,088 --> 00:50:37,968
Do you think you can play along?

510
00:50:38,090 --> 00:50:40,137
- Yes, sir.
- Great.

511
00:50:40,301 --> 00:50:42,682
Because, otherwise I'll erase your ass.

512
00:51:00,905 --> 00:51:05,114
Taxi! You need a taxi sir?
I got magazines, I got music, I got whisky.

513
00:51:05,117 --> 00:51:07,456
You need a cab man?
Come on!

514
00:51:33,145 --> 00:51:34,525
Good afternoon. Can I help you?

515
00:51:34,647 --> 00:51:37,153
Yes I would like to have a room, please.

516
00:51:42,321 --> 00:51:45,582
Nice to have you back with us, Mr. Brubaker.
Would you like the same suite?

517
00:51:45,586 --> 00:51:46,862
Well. Definitely.

518
00:51:48,994 --> 00:51:51,000
It seems you left something in our safe.

519
00:51:51,163 --> 00:51:52,261
Could you get it please?

520
00:51:58,379 --> 00:51:59,884
Identification?

521
00:52:09,306 --> 00:52:11,825
- I'll go encode your room key.
- Thank you.

522
00:52:28,200 --> 00:52:31,535
- There you go, Mr. Brubaker. Suite 610 in the east wing.
- Thank you.

523
00:52:31,537 --> 00:52:34,139
- Could I borrow your pen, please?
- Certainly.

524
00:52:46,093 --> 00:52:47,264
Thank you.

525
00:52:52,558 --> 00:52:54,980
Hey, man, you need a cab?

526
00:52:55,144 --> 00:52:59,687
- What was wrong with this one?
- He ain't got five kids to feed.

527
00:52:59,690 --> 00:53:02,029
- Where's yours?
- Right over there man.

528
00:53:04,445 --> 00:53:07,118
Hey, asshole!
That's my fare!

529
00:53:07,281 --> 00:53:08,577
Eat this!

530
00:53:08,741 --> 00:53:09,996
Damn you, Benny!

531
00:53:16,248 --> 00:53:18,095
Welcome to Mars, man!

532
00:53:22,088 --> 00:53:25,754
- What the hell was that, an accident?
- That's the rebels man.

533
00:53:25,758 --> 00:53:27,138
Let's get outta here...

534
00:53:27,259 --> 00:53:29,098
...before they arrest us!

535
00:53:29,261 --> 00:53:31,354
What do the rebels want?

536
00:53:31,355 --> 00:53:34,658
All the usual.
More money, more freedom, more air.

537
00:53:39,605 --> 00:53:40,978
So, where to?

538
00:53:40,981 --> 00:53:42,695
The Last Resort.

539
00:53:42,817 --> 00:53:44,780
You're getting off to an early start.

540
00:53:45,778 --> 00:53:47,950
- First time on Mars?
- Yes.

541
00:53:48,114 --> 00:53:49,869
Well, actually, no.

542
00:53:50,032 --> 00:53:51,704
Well, sort of.

543
00:53:51,867 --> 00:53:55,971
Damn! The man don't even know whether
he's been to Mars or not.

544
00:54:06,257 --> 00:54:08,596
Voila. Venusville.

545
00:54:09,969 --> 00:54:12,183
Hey, you see anything you like?

546
00:54:16,308 --> 00:54:19,685
End of the line.
We're going to have to walk from here.

547
00:54:19,687 --> 00:54:21,525
I'll show you where.

548
00:54:21,689 --> 00:54:25,523
- Do you want to know the future?
- What about the past?

549
00:54:25,526 --> 00:54:29,320
Come on. It's around the corner, right down this alley.

550
00:54:29,321 --> 00:54:31,202
They got everything.

551
00:54:33,826 --> 00:54:35,706
Not bad, huh?

552
00:54:37,246 --> 00:54:41,875
Read your palm? Your mind? Read your aura?
Probe the secrets of your heart?

553
00:54:41,876 --> 00:54:44,081
- I bet I can guess your birthday.
- What is it?

554
00:54:44,084 --> 00:54:47,106
- You're a Taurus, right?
- How did you guess?

555
00:54:49,675 --> 00:54:51,989
- Tell me something; are all psychics, uh...?
- Freaks?

556
00:54:52,052 --> 00:54:54,116
Afraid so, man.
It goes with the territory.

557
00:54:54,180 --> 00:54:59,431
- What happened to them?
- Cheap domes. And no air to screen of the rays.

558
00:54:59,435 --> 00:55:03,639
So, there it is. The Last Resort.
You sure you want to go in here man?

559
00:55:03,642 --> 00:55:06,730
- Why not?
- I know this much better place down the street--

560
00:55:06,734 --> 00:55:09,735
The girls are cleaner, the liquor ain't watered down--

561
00:55:09,737 --> 00:55:11,909
Sure, and you get kickback.

562
00:55:12,073 --> 00:55:14,912
Hey, man, I got five kids to feed.

563
00:55:15,076 --> 00:55:16,914
Take them to the dentist.

564
00:55:17,036 --> 00:55:19,758
Hey, Thanks! Mister!
Listen, I'll be waiting here for you.

565
00:55:19,762 --> 00:55:22,919
You just take your time.
Benny's the name. Benny!

566
00:55:41,894 --> 00:55:43,999
- What do you want?
- I'm looking for Melina.

567
00:55:44,063 --> 00:55:45,735
She's busy.

568
00:55:45,898 --> 00:55:47,903
But Mary here, she's free.

569
00:55:48,025 --> 00:55:53,327
Well, Not "free" honey, but available.

570
00:55:56,575 --> 00:55:58,831
Thanks.
I'll wait for Melina.

571
00:55:58,994 --> 00:56:00,166
Earth slime.

572
00:56:00,287 --> 00:56:02,918
Thing is, friend, Mel's real picky.

573
00:56:03,082 --> 00:56:05,129
She kinda sticks to her regulars.

574
00:56:05,292 --> 00:56:07,173
She will like me.

575
00:56:08,379 --> 00:56:09,675
Mel!

576
00:56:47,460 --> 00:56:48,673
Hello Hauser.

577
00:56:49,795 --> 00:56:51,676
Still bulging, I see.

578
00:56:53,215 --> 00:56:56,569
- What you been feeding this thing?
- Blondes.

579
00:56:58,429 --> 00:57:00,267
I think it's still hungry.

580
00:57:02,725 --> 00:57:05,850
You got a lot of nerve showing
your face around here, Hauser.

581
00:57:05,853 --> 00:57:07,817
Look who's talking.

582
00:57:07,980 --> 00:57:10,695
Hey Tony. Give the big guy a break.

583
00:57:10,858 --> 00:57:13,114
Relax. You'll live longer.

584
00:57:13,277 --> 00:57:14,615
Come on.

585
00:57:20,326 --> 00:57:24,034
- Honey, take care of Tony, will you?
- No problem.

586
00:57:24,038 --> 00:57:27,099
If you need any help with this one,
give me a holler.

587
00:57:41,847 --> 00:57:43,853
You son of a bitch.

588
00:57:43,974 --> 00:57:46,902
You're alive?
I thought that Cohaagen tortured you to death.

589
00:57:46,905 --> 00:57:48,641
Well, I guess he didn't.

590
00:57:48,644 --> 00:57:52,741
And you couldn't get me a message?
You never wondered what happened to me?

591
00:58:00,032 --> 00:58:02,246
Hauser, thank God you're alive.

592
00:58:03,452 --> 00:58:06,708
Melin-- Melina.
Melina.

593
00:58:07,790 --> 00:58:10,688
- There's something I have to tell you...
- What?

594
00:58:10,709 --> 00:58:14,418
- I don't remember you.
- What are you talking about?

595
00:58:14,422 --> 00:58:16,469
I don't remember you.

596
00:58:16,632 --> 00:58:20,194
I don't remember us.
I don't even remember me.

597
00:58:22,179 --> 00:58:24,678
What, did you get amnesia?
How did you get here?

598
00:58:24,682 --> 00:58:27,139
- Hauser left me a note.
- Hauser? You're Hauser.

599
00:58:27,143 --> 00:58:28,981
Not anymore.

600
00:58:29,145 --> 00:58:32,193
Now I'm Quaid.
Douglas Quaid.

601
00:58:35,443 --> 00:58:39,568
- Hauser, you've lost your mind.
- I didn't lose my mind. Cohaagen stole it.

602
00:58:39,572 --> 00:58:44,240
He found out that Hauser switched sides,
so he turned him into somebody else: me.

603
00:58:44,243 --> 00:58:45,581
This is too weird.

604
00:58:45,745 --> 00:58:48,412
Then he dumped me on Earth
with a wife and a lousy job and--

605
00:58:48,414 --> 00:58:51,415
Did you say wife?
Are you fucking married?

606
00:58:51,417 --> 00:58:53,499
- I'm sure she wasn't really my wife.
- Oh, she isn't really your wife.

607
00:58:53,502 --> 00:58:56,050
How stupid of me.
She was Hauser's wife?

608
00:58:56,053 --> 00:58:58,964
- Look forget that I said wife.
- No. Let's just forget everything.

609
00:58:58,966 --> 00:59:02,862
- I'm sick of hearing your goddamn lies.
- Why would I lie to you?

610
00:59:03,763 --> 00:59:07,223
Because you're still working for Cohaagen.

611
00:59:07,224 --> 00:59:09,772
Don't be ridiculous.

612
00:59:12,438 --> 00:59:16,760
You never loved me, Hauser.
You just used me to get inside.

613
00:59:16,817 --> 00:59:18,656
Inside what?

614
00:59:22,865 --> 00:59:24,829
I think you'd better leave.

615
00:59:24,992 --> 00:59:28,325
- Melina, Hauser sent me to do something.
- I'm not falling for it.

616
00:59:28,329 --> 00:59:30,578
He said there's enough in here
to nail Cohaagen for good.

617
00:59:30,581 --> 00:59:32,580
- Get out!
- You've got to help me remember!

618
00:59:32,583 --> 00:59:34,630
- I said, get out!
- Melina, please!

619
00:59:34,794 --> 00:59:36,632
People are trying to kill me.

620
00:59:37,588 --> 00:59:39,176
Really?

621
00:59:41,592 --> 00:59:43,797
All right, I'm leaving.

622
00:59:55,689 --> 00:59:58,691
Baby, you make me wish I had three hands.

623
00:59:58,692 --> 01:00:01,365
Well I think you're doing just fine with two.

624
01:00:01,487 --> 01:00:03,986
Excuse me, baby.
We'll pick this up later.

625
01:00:03,989 --> 01:00:06,329
Hey, that didn't take long.

626
01:00:06,492 --> 01:00:09,158
Listen! Let me ask you a question.
Did you ever fuck a mutant?

627
01:00:09,161 --> 01:00:11,662
- Take me to the hotel.
- I know these Siamese twins.

628
01:00:11,664 --> 01:00:14,391
Man, you don't know if you're coming or going.

629
01:00:24,051 --> 01:00:30,143
This afternoon at 4:30 p.m., I signed an order
declaring martial law throughout the Mars federal colony.

630
01:00:30,307 --> 01:00:34,975
I will not tolerate any further damage
to our mineral export operations.

631
01:00:34,979 --> 01:00:38,748
Mr. Kuato and his terrorists must
understand that their self-defeating efforts...

632
01:00:38,749 --> 01:00:40,849
...will only bring misery and suffering to the people--

633
01:00:44,280 --> 01:00:45,451
Mr. Quaid?

634
01:00:46,282 --> 01:00:47,453
What?

635
01:00:47,616 --> 01:00:49,872
I need to talk to you about Mr. Hauser.

636
01:00:51,162 --> 01:00:53,537
- Who are you?
- Dr. Edgemar from Rekall.

637
01:00:53,539 --> 01:00:55,955
- How did you find me?
- It's a little difficult to explain.

638
01:00:55,958 --> 01:00:58,856
Could you open the door, please?
I'm not armed.

639
01:01:00,546 --> 01:01:03,469
Don't worry. I'm alone.
May I come in?

640
01:01:05,551 --> 01:01:08,968
- What do you want?   - This is going to be
very difficult for you at accept, Mr. Quaid.

641
01:01:08,971 --> 01:01:12,575
- I'm listening.
- I'm afraid you're not really standing here right now.

642
01:01:14,143 --> 01:01:17,394
- Ya know, Doc, you could have fooled me.
- I'm quite serious.

643
01:01:17,396 --> 01:01:20,653
You're not here and neither am I.

644
01:01:20,816 --> 01:01:21,988
That's amazing.

645
01:01:22,151 --> 01:01:25,157
- Where are we?
- At Rekall.

646
01:01:25,321 --> 01:01:30,359
You're strapped into an implant chair and
I'm monitoring you at from the psychoprobe console.

647
01:01:31,285 --> 01:01:33,791
Ah, I get it.
I'm dreaming.

648
01:01:33,913 --> 01:01:37,371
And this is all part of that delightful
vacation your company has sold me.

649
01:01:37,374 --> 01:01:38,713
Not exactly.

650
01:01:38,876 --> 01:01:43,085
What you're experiencing is a free-form
delusion based on our memory tapes.

651
01:01:43,089 --> 01:01:45,774
But you're inventing it yourself as you go along.

652
01:01:47,051 --> 01:01:50,594
Well, if this is my delusion,
who the hell invited you?

653
01:01:50,596 --> 01:01:54,598
I've been artificially implanted
as an emergency measure.

654
01:01:54,600 --> 01:01:58,017
I'm sorry to tell you this, Mr. Quaid,
but you've suffered a schizoid embolism.

655
01:01:58,020 --> 01:02:00,317
We can't snap you out of your fantasy...

656
01:02:00,439 --> 01:02:03,606
...and I've been sent in to try to talk you down.

657
01:02:03,609 --> 01:02:05,828
How much is Cohaagen paying you for this?

658
01:02:06,987 --> 01:02:11,197
Think about it. Your dream started
in the middle of the implant procedure.

659
01:02:11,200 --> 01:02:13,699
Everything after that--
the chases, the trip to Mars...

660
01:02:13,702 --> 01:02:18,287
...your suite here at the Hilton--these are all
elements of your Rekall Holiday and Ego Trip:

661
01:02:18,290 --> 01:02:20,629
You paid to be a secret agent.

662
01:02:20,793 --> 01:02:23,174
Bullshit. It's coincidence.

663
01:02:23,337 --> 01:02:25,843
And what about the girl?

664
01:02:25,965 --> 01:02:28,679
Brunette, athletic, sleazy and demure?

665
01:02:28,843 --> 01:02:31,467
Just like you specified.
Is that a coincidence?

666
01:02:31,470 --> 01:02:35,139
She's real.
I dreamed about her before I even went to Rekall.

667
01:02:35,141 --> 01:02:37,146
Mr. Quaid.

668
01:02:37,309 --> 01:02:41,435
Can you hear yourself?
She's real because you dreamed her?

669
01:02:41,439 --> 01:02:44,522
- That's right.
- Maybe this will convince you.

670
01:02:44,525 --> 01:02:46,906
Would you mind opening the door?

671
01:02:48,946 --> 01:02:51,243
- You open it.
- No need to be rude.

672
01:02:51,407 --> 01:02:53,162
I'll do it.

673
01:02:59,832 --> 01:03:01,003
Sweetheart?

674
01:03:03,669 --> 01:03:05,633
Come in, Mrs. Quaid.

675
01:03:09,884 --> 01:03:15,645
- What I suppose you're not here either?
- I'm here at Rekall.

676
01:03:19,351 --> 01:03:20,940
I love you.

677
01:03:21,103 --> 01:03:24,402
Right.
That's why you tried to kill me.

678
01:03:24,523 --> 01:03:28,489
No. I'd never do anything to hurt you.

679
01:03:28,652 --> 01:03:30,908
I want you to come back to me.

680
01:03:33,115 --> 01:03:36,448
- Bullshit.
- What's bullshit, Mr. Quaid?

681
01:03:36,452 --> 01:03:41,120
That you're having a paranoid episode
triggered by acute neuro-chemical trauma?

682
01:03:41,123 --> 01:03:45,166
Or that you're really an
invincible secret agent from Mars...

683
01:03:45,169 --> 01:03:51,161
...who's the victim of an interplanetary conspiracy
to make him think he's a lowly construction worker?

684
01:03:59,016 --> 01:04:01,272
Stop punishing yourself, Doug.

685
01:04:01,393 --> 01:04:04,455
You're a fine, upstanding man.
You have a beautiful wife that loves you.

686
01:04:05,898 --> 01:04:07,778
Your whole life is ahead of you.

687
01:04:09,819 --> 01:04:12,588
But you've got to want to return to reality.

688
01:04:14,740 --> 01:04:17,513
Let's assume I do. Then what?

689
01:04:20,329 --> 01:04:23,336
- Swallow this.
- What is it?

690
01:04:23,499 --> 01:04:27,416
It's a symbol of your desire to return to reality.

691
01:04:27,420 --> 01:04:29,759
Inside your dream, you'll fall asleep.

692
01:04:33,759 --> 01:04:38,052
All right, let's say you're telling
the truth and this is all a dream.

693
01:04:38,055 --> 01:04:41,024
Then I could pull this trigger,
and it won't matter.

694
01:04:41,028 --> 01:04:43,934
- Doug, don't.
- It won't make the slightest difference to me, Doug,...

695
01:04:43,936 --> 01:04:48,641
...but the consequences to you would be devastating.
In your mind I'll be dead.

696
01:04:48,644 --> 01:04:51,984
And with no one to guide you out,
you'll be stuck in permanent psychosis.

697
01:04:51,986 --> 01:04:54,458
Doug, let Dr. Edgemar help you.

698
01:04:54,461 --> 01:04:56,822
The walls of reality will come crashing down.

699
01:04:56,824 --> 01:05:00,366
In one minute you'll be the savior of the rebel cause,
and the next thing you know...

700
01:05:00,369 --> 01:05:02,458
...you'll be Cohaagen's bosom buddy.

701
01:05:02,621 --> 01:05:06,622
You even have fantasies about alien civilizations,
as you requested.

702
01:05:06,625 --> 01:05:09,436
But in the end,
back on earth you'll be lobotomized!

703
01:05:11,881 --> 01:05:15,442
So get a grip on yourself, Doug.
And put down that gun!

704
01:05:21,307 --> 01:05:24,660
Good.
Now take the pill and put it in your mouth.

705
01:05:29,315 --> 01:05:31,404
Swallow it!

706
01:05:33,944 --> 01:05:36,409
Go ahead, sweetheart.

707
01:05:59,178 --> 01:06:02,835
Now you've done it.
Now you've done it!

708
01:06:23,369 --> 01:06:25,750
That's for making me come to Mars.

709
01:06:27,123 --> 01:06:30,142
You know how much I hate this fucking planet!

710
01:06:32,461 --> 01:06:33,632
Cuff him.

711
01:06:40,344 --> 01:06:43,822
- I got him.
- Good bring him down to the service elevator.

712
01:06:46,016 --> 01:06:47,355
Let's go.

713
01:08:00,841 --> 01:08:02,429
Fuck you!

714
01:08:12,895 --> 01:08:13,993
Doug.

715
01:08:15,731 --> 01:08:17,737
Honey...

716
01:08:17,900 --> 01:08:20,586
...you wouldn't hurt me, would you, sweetheart?

717
01:08:22,238 --> 01:08:25,453
Sweetheart, be reasonable.

718
01:08:25,616 --> 01:08:27,621
After all, we're married.

719
01:08:33,290 --> 01:08:34,628
Consider that a divorce.

720
01:08:37,169 --> 01:08:38,799
That was your wife?

721
01:08:42,800 --> 01:08:44,138
What a bitch.

722
01:08:52,351 --> 01:08:54,357
Hey, get out of the way!

723
01:08:56,897 --> 01:08:59,403
I thought you didn't like me.

724
01:08:59,525 --> 01:09:02,526
If Cohaagen wants you dead, you might be okay.

725
01:09:02,528 --> 01:09:05,945
